The child was discovered crying in a blood-stained plastic bag by refuse workers as they emptied the bin at the bottom of a rubbish chute on a housing estate. The youngster could have been crushed if the cleaners had not found him, said a politician. Police said the child, whose birth parents have not been named, had no visible injuries but was taken to hospital. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Authorities say he is in a stable condition. Now six women have written to The New Paper offering to take care of him. In comments published by the publication, Shahirah Slamat, 34, said: “I am willing to do anything for the baby. Source: News Sky 